headline: Dividend Stock CMS Energy Powers Blend Of Growth, Yield, Stability
summary: Headquartered in Jackson, Mich., CMS Energy plays a pivotal role as the primary power provider in that state, delivering electricity and gas to 6.8 million of Michigan's 10 million residents.  For a utility, CMS Energy has demonstrated solid growth.  The company boasts a three-year annual EPS growth rate of 9%, a trend that is expected to continue.
